\begin_layout Standard
A crisis is: a collapse of large financial institutions (or a fear of it)
 or a malfunctioning of important financial markets (even a potential one).
 For example, in 2008 the value of big banks around the world went down
 dramatically.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How do we measure short-term and long-term risk of financial institutions?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
LIBOR
\series default
 - the (3 months) average of interest rates at which large banks lend to
 each other.
 It acts as an index to set cost of variable-rate loans.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is usually close the the CB interest rate, but might differ significantly
 when there is lack of confidence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
OIS
\series default
 - interest rate used to swap transactions in the money market (like the
 CB interest rate).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The LIBOR-OIS spread is a key measure of the 
\series bold
short-run
\series default
 credit risk in the banking sector.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
CDS
\series default
 (credit default swap) - an insurance contract against a default of another
 entity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During the 2008 crisis, the LIBOR-OIS spread jumped by more than 7 times.
 As the short-term risk increased, the long-term risk increased as well.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Quantitative Easing
\series default
 (QE) - large scale asset purchases by a CB.
 Might be appropriate when short-term interest rates are near 0, and standard
 monetary policy is not effective anymore.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The COVID-19 global recession is caused both by 
\series bold
demand & supply shocks
\series default
, which lead to market instability due to uncertainity.
 The economic activity is reduced and many businesses collapse.
 The ability to work has decreased, there is negative impact on employment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
CBs around the world initiated huge, 
\series bold
unprecedented
\series default
 QEs during the COVID-19 pandemic.
 Each action taken now is 
\series bold
multiplied by several times
\series default
, compared to actions done in the previous crisis.
\end_layout

